<TITLE> 3 more made secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)  The government on Monday promoted three additional secretary-ranked bureaucrats to secretaries, and made them OSDs at the establishment ministry pending assignment. An establishment ministry circular Monday said Bangladesh Handloom Board chairman Abdul Kakim Mandal, additional secretary for social welfare Sunil Kanti Ghosh and Bangladesh Fisheries Development Corporation chairman Mohammad Shahjahan were elevated to the rank of secretary. They have been made officers on special duty at the establishment ministry until their next assignments, the circular said. The ministry in another order Monday appointed cabinet division joint secretary Mohammad Moyeenuddin Abdullah as director general of the prime minister's office. Abdullah will replace MAM Siddique, who has been appointed director general of the BEPZA board's executive cell. Bangladesh Tea Board chairman Brig Gen Mahbubur Rahman Khan has been posted back to the army. Among four recently promoted secretaries ASM Ali Kabir has been made establishment secretary, Abdus Subhan Sikder shipping secretary, M Quamrul Alam Rabbani Bangladesh Shipping Corporation chairman and M Nazmul Huda Khan science and ICT secretary. Three deputy secretary-level officers and a senior assistant secretary saw inter-ministerial transfers on Monday, according to the order. bdnews2
